	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-06-26T01:50:44">SIG Plc is a United Kingdom-based distributor of specialist building products in Europe. The Company is engaged in is the supply of specialist products to construction and related markets. The Company product and service offering's three core markets include insulation and energy management, interior fit out and roofing products. The Company operates in two segments: UK &amp; Ireland and Mainland Europe. The Company trades under various names, including SIG Insulation, SIG Technical Insulation, SIG Interiors, SIG Construction Accessories and SIG Fixings. It supplies insulation and related products in Europe, the United Kingdom, Ireland, Germany, Poland and France. It supplies exterior roofing products in the United Kingdom and Ireland, France and Poland. It supplies products required for the interior fit out of non-residential buildings in Europe.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2016-01-28T05:54:37">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 June 2015, SIG plc revenues decreased 3% to L1.24B. Net income remained flat at L18.3M. Revenues reflect Mainland Europe segment decrease of 13% to L570M, France segment decrease of 13% to L261.7M, Germany/Austria segment decrease of 13% to L178.7M,  Attributable to Business divested segment decrease from L21.6M to L0K. Net income reflects Uk &amp; Ireland segment income totaling L19.8M vs. loss of L3.5M.</Text>
	</TextInfo>
